  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Eliza Wigham gives additional information about the articles sent to the bazaar. Miss Massie was advised to forward some London contributions through Glasgow. Wigham mentions especially the &quot;valuable volumes of Handel&apos;s Oratorios.&quot; There is also a case of dried plant specimens and an autograph of De Quincy. Wigham writes: &quot;The cause has lost a valuable friend by the death of old Miss Miller of Perth in her 93&apos;d year---her last labour of love was sending her contribution to Boston a very short time before her death.&quot;</subfield>
